<paragraph blockId="16.[168,778,1055,1288]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1094,1118]" pageId="16" pageNumber="523">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity box="[651,778,1094,1118]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.25" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="523" unit="m" value="0.625" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.15">0.15–1.1 m</quantity>
height. Characterized by its leaf-blades glabrous, or sometimes hairy, plane and convolute, 
<quantity box="[585,679,1162,1186]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="16" pageNumber="523" unit="cm" value="33.5" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="7.0">7–60 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[168,289,1196,1220]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="523" unit="cm" value="0.3" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.5 cm</quantity>
wide, with a clear and conspicuous central vein. Spikelets in a typical panicle, 
<quantity box="[563,658,1230,1254]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="16" pageNumber="523" unit="cm" value="14.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="8.0">8–20 cm</quantity>
long, with scattered hairs.
</paragraph>
